<h1>Get Points</h1>
<p class="lead">
	<p>Recognize a fellow Poinster!</p>

	<p class="leader_text">Think your fellow employee did an amazing job worthy of recognition? Give 'em some Points! Employees with the most points at the end of the year will receive special recognition and rewards, so don't hesistate to celebrate hard work with a gift of points!</p>

</p>

<div class="get">
	<form class="give" method="post" action="/account/give-points">
		<select name="points">
  			<option value="0">I did the following awesome thing...</option>
  			<option value="1000">I volunteered for one hour.</option>
  			<option value="4000">I volunteered for 4 hours.</option>
  			<option value="8000">I volunteered for a full day.</option>					
  			<option value="2500">I participated in a "Points For Good" activity!</option>
  			<option value="10000">I organized a volunteer activity for 5 or more Poinsters!</option>
		</select>
		<input class="textfield" type="text" name="message" placeholder="Tell us more about what you did." required />
		<input type="submit" value="Get My Points!" />
	</form>
</div>
